<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9201> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9201" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 732, footnote 71" ;
	dprr:hasID 9201 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2607> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2607" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected to assign unoccupied lands in Liguria and Gaul to individual settlers, ten iugera each to Romans, three each to Latins (Liv. 42.4.3-4)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2607 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2604> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2604" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This Decemvir may possibly be identified with no. 96, the Pr. Peregrinus of 184, but the consul of 181 who transferred the Ligures Corneliani to Samnium in 180 would probably be selected to assign Ligurian land." ;
	dprr:hasID 2604 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2452> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2452" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His imperium prorogued in Liguria, he transferred the Apuani to Samnium, and celebrated a triumph (Liv. 40.36.7, 37.8-38.9; see Degrassi 554). See above, on Baebius." ;
	dprr:hasID 2452 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2451> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2451" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On this cognomen, see 181, note 1." ;
	dprr:hasID 2451 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2408> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2408" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Nep. Hann. 13.1; Liv. 40.18.1, and 35.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.; Val. Max. 1.1.12; 2.5.1; Plin. NH 13.85, with Cass. Hem.{384} fr. 37 Peter; Plut. Num. 22.5; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Both Consuls were assigned to Liguria and Baebius returned to hold the elections (Liv. 40.18.3, 26.5-6, and 35.1). They instituted the first bribery law (Liv. 40.12.11; cf. FOR 1.54f., 187; Schol. Bob. 2.78 Stangl); and Baebius a law to require the election of 4 and 6 Praetors, respectively, on alternate years (Liv. 40.44.2; cf. FOR 1.54f., 187)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2408 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2407> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2407" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The name Cethegus is attested by the Fast. Cap., by Cassius Hemina in Pliny (loc. cit.), and by Sulpicius Blitho in Nepos (loc. cit.). Lentulus therefore in Livy, and from him in Valerius Maximus, is simply a mistake.{387}" ;
	dprr:hasID 2407 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2319> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2319" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Maxis (95) and Stella Maranca (306) identify the Consul of 181 with the Praetor of 184. I have given Münzer's identification here.{374}" ;
	dprr:hasID 2319 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2317> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2317" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elections: Liv. 39.23.2 Provinces omitted in Livy." ;
	dprr:hasID 2317 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2296> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2296" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 39.7.8-9. On Postumius, see Lübker no. 3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2296 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10030> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10030" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Liguribus Apuaneis. MRR I.388, Itgenshorst no. 187, Rich no. 186." ;
	dprr:hasID 10030 .
